#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:5
msgid "Write your own style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:7
msgid ""
"So, how to create a style? All you have to do is to subclass `Style` and "
"define some styles:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:10
msgid ""
"from pygments.style import Style\n"
"from pygments.token import Token, Comment, Keyword, Name, String, \\\n"
"     Error, Generic, Number, Operator\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class YourStyle(Style):\n"
"\n"
"    styles = {\n"
"        Token:                  '',\n"
"        Comment:                'italic #888',\n"
"        Keyword:                'bold #005',\n"
"        Name:                   '#f00',\n"
"        Name.Class:             'bold #0f0',\n"
"        Name.Function:          '#0f0',\n"
"        String:                 'bg:#eee #111'\n"
"    }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:29
msgid ""
"That's it, save it as ``your.py``. There are just a few rules. When you "
"define a style for `Name` the style automatically also affects `Name."
"Function` and so on. If you defined ``'bold'`` and you don't want boldface "
"for a subtoken use ``'nobold'``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:33
msgid ""
"(Philosophy: the styles aren't written in CSS syntax since this way they can "
"be used for a variety of formatters.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:36
msgid "``Token`` is the default style inherited by all token types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:38
msgid "To make the style usable for Pygments, you must"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:40
msgid "either register it as a plugin (see :doc:`the plugin docs <plugins>`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:41
msgid "or update the ``pygments.styles`` subpackage directory. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:43
msgid "add ``your.py`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:44
msgid "regenerate the mappings file using ``tox -e mapfiles``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:48
msgid ""
"You should *only* add it to the ``pygments.styles`` subdirectory if you are "
"working on a contribution to Pygments. You should not use that method to "
"extend an already existing copy of Pygments, use the plugins mechanism for "
"that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:55
msgid "Style Rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:57
msgid "Here a small overview of all allowed styles:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:59
msgid "``bold``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:60
msgid "render text as bold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:61
msgid "``nobold``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:62
msgid "don't render text as bold (to prevent subtokens being highlighted bold)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:63
msgid "``italic``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:64
msgid "render text italic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:65
msgid "``noitalic``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:66
msgid "don't render text as italic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:67
msgid "``underline``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:68
msgid "render text underlined"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:69
msgid "``nounderline``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:70
msgid "don't render text underlined"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:71
msgid "``bg:``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:72
msgid "transparent background"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:73
msgid "``bg:#000000``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:74
msgid "background color (black)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:75
msgid "``border:``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:76
msgid "no border"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:77
msgid "``border:#ffffff``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:78
msgid "border color (white)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:79
msgid "``#ff0000``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:80
msgid "text color (red)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:81
msgid "``noinherit``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:82
msgid "don't inherit styles from supertoken"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:84
msgid ""
"Note that there may not be a space between ``bg:`` and the color value since "
"the style definition string is split at whitespace. Also, using named colors "
"is not allowed since the supported color names vary for different formatters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/styledevelopment.rst:89
msgid "Furthermore, not all lexers might support every style."
msgstr ""
